The world

The oldest tradition of our world has always been the drinking of wine. Barrel-chested men drinking bottles in saunas with the wind outside, lovers sharing the taste of the same wine on each other's lips, friends facing feasts in rooms and in stairways...
Wine is magic and magic is wine. A glass a day is good for your soul, and for your body. GOWAD (glass of wine a day) this winter and make sure to write a poem or a tweet after your daily drink.

The year is 1963, you are a young "stilyaga" - style hunter - in the city of Novosibirsk, the Soviet Union. You wear brand clothes, illegally smuggled through the border. Flannel shirt, a slightly unfitting sport coat with a wild pattern - just like one of those American actors.

Every day I am saddened I did not live through the rot and the fall of the USSR. The stories I have been told about that age! The subcultures, all imitating each other, the secret clubs with tables of cocaine, the Church regaining her power, the mafiosos circling the streets...
Wear a scarf, surprisingly warms you up a lot
